WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

01:46.315 --> 01:48.192
Straight through to
the conservatory.

01:50.361 --> 01:54.782
<i>One always expected Mike to get the
nod after a lifetime's loyal service.</i>

01:55.950 --> 01:58.536
That's not to take away
from cbes and obes.

01:59.578 --> 02:02.665
Of course, any order of the British
empire is a huge achievement.

02:04.917 --> 02:06.085
No...

02:07.044 --> 02:08.378
Uh, yes, that's for the kitchen.

02:10.548 --> 02:14.552
Didn't Luke's school dinner lady
get an mbe a couple of years ago?

02:15.219 --> 02:18.097
Yes. Mbes tend to be for more...

02:18.347 --> 02:20.766
- Hands on service.
- Hmm.

02:21.559 --> 02:25.688
So, will you be expecting us to
call you lady abbott from now on?

02:25.813 --> 02:29.608
Not necessarily, but it does
have a rather nice ring to it.

02:30.317 --> 02:31.797
Come on. Let's have
a naughty Sherry.

02:33.362 --> 02:35.656
- Not over there!
- Sorry, ma'am.

02:38.576 --> 02:42.663
<i>During my four decades on the beat,
I've worked with some fantastic people.</i>

02:43.330 --> 02:44.933
I've also had the pleasure

02:44.957 --> 02:47.751
of working with a number
of great partners.

02:47.877 --> 02:49.128
Aw.

02:49.420 --> 02:52.214
Not in the biblical
sense of course.

02:52.339 --> 02:53.507
Joking aside,

02:54.049 --> 02:55.885
there's been one
very special person

02:56.468 --> 02:59.680
who has walked the thin blue line
with me every step of the way,

03:00.097 --> 03:02.641
throughout every trial,
case and verdict,

03:03.475 --> 03:06.770
and that is my wife of 35
years, lady Sandra abbott.

03:06.937 --> 03:08.022
Aw.

03:08.564 --> 03:09.690
Thank you.

03:20.492 --> 03:24.055
Are you losing sleep about what's going
to be happening from here on in?

03:24.079 --> 03:25.497
No, thank you. What do you mean?

03:26.040 --> 03:27.625
When Hugo retired,

03:27.917 --> 03:30.896
I was on the verge of getting
a part-time job in waitrose

03:30.920 --> 03:32.004
just to get away from him.

03:32.171 --> 03:33.773
I'm not concerned
about that, Janet.

03:33.797 --> 03:36.258
I've been planning our retirement
for the last 35 years.

03:36.800 --> 03:38.344
Oh, well, good for you, darling.

03:39.011 --> 03:41.513
- Top up?
- Oh, lovely. I'll spend a penny.

03:44.141 --> 03:46.185
- Oh, are you enjoying it?
- Marvellous!

04:01.659 --> 04:02.969
What the hell's going on?

04:02.993 --> 04:04.286
We were just...

04:04.620 --> 04:06.163
It's not what it
looks like, Sandra.

04:08.249 --> 04:09.249
Sandra?

04:09.792 --> 04:10.792
Sandra!

04:11.585 --> 04:12.585
Sandra!

04:13.379 --> 04:15.398
- Sandra, wait!
- Get off me!

04:15.422 --> 04:17.702
- How long has it been going on?
- Let's not do this here.

04:17.726 --> 04:19.903
- How long, Mike?
- Since we all went to sorrento.

04:19.927 --> 04:20.927
Oh, bloody hell.

04:21.387 --> 04:23.180
That's nearly five years ago.

04:24.014 --> 04:26.201
I've had enough of all
this hide-and-seek, Mike.

04:26.225 --> 04:27.768
How could you do this to me?

04:28.060 --> 04:29.645
You're supposed to be my friend.

04:29.937 --> 04:31.855
We even took you to the palace.

04:32.231 --> 04:35.627
I... I didn't mean for
this to happen, Sandra.

04:35.651 --> 04:38.171
Oh, really? You knew precisely
what you were doing!

04:38.195 --> 04:40.882
Now, please calm down, Sandra.
Remember where you are.

04:40.906 --> 04:43.242
I know exactly where I am.
I'm in my own bloody home.

04:44.618 --> 04:48.348
I have spent my entire married life
putting you and your career first,

04:48.372 --> 04:50.653
and what got me through was
knowing that when you retired,

04:50.677 --> 04:52.644
we would share our
golden years together.

04:52.668 --> 04:53.919
But instead,

04:54.295 --> 04:56.898
you've traded me in
for a newer model.

04:56.922 --> 04:58.674
Let me tell you, Mike,

04:58.882 --> 05:01.361
she's had more than
one previous owner!

05:01.385 --> 05:05.347
And, and her bodywork
is mainly filler!

05:06.098 --> 05:07.098
Mum!

05:07.766 --> 05:09.935
- Dad, what have you done?
- Sandra...

05:11.020 --> 05:12.038
Sandra?

05:12.062 --> 05:13.564
Sandra!

05:22.281 --> 05:23.365
Sandra?

05:24.366 --> 05:26.035
Sandra!

05:26.660 --> 05:28.245
Please, let me explain.

05:29.163 --> 05:31.790
The last thing I wanted
to do was to hurt you.

05:32.041 --> 05:36.045
I know it must seem like I've
behaved in a terrible way, but...

05:36.920 --> 05:39.048
Look, one thing led
to another and...

05:39.965 --> 05:41.717
Oh, you know how it is.

05:57.358 --> 05:58.793
- Hello, Emma.
- Hi.

05:58.817 --> 06:00.361
Ooh!

06:00.778 --> 06:01.904
Woo-hoo!

06:15.167 --> 06:16.167
Excuse me!

06:16.585 --> 06:18.253
It's women only in here.

06:20.714 --> 06:21.733
Oi!

06:21.757 --> 06:23.509
That's my handbag!

06:23.717 --> 06:25.803
Come back here, you... wait!

06:31.683 --> 06:33.227
Gotcha.

06:35.020 --> 06:36.146
Charlie!

06:36.480 --> 06:39.066
Yeah, all ready to
go this end, Ted.

06:39.650 --> 06:41.527
- Bilge filter.
- Check!

06:42.194 --> 06:43.654
Rodding junction.

06:44.279 --> 06:46.383
- Check.
- Pump outlet.

06:46.407 --> 06:49.118
Oil filter tank?
Discharge connection?

06:49.243 --> 06:51.096
Check, check, check!

06:51.120 --> 06:52.538
Then we're good to go.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.123
I'll start her up.

06:57.835 --> 07:00.045
- She's sounding good, Charlie.
- Yeah.

07:04.007 --> 07:05.175
What's that?

07:05.926 --> 07:07.261
Jubilee clip.

07:07.719 --> 07:08.804
Where from?

07:09.388 --> 07:10.782
Oh, bollocks.

07:10.806 --> 07:12.367
Stop! Stop! Oh!

07:12.391 --> 07:14.017
Flipping hell!

07:14.518 --> 07:15.978
- Turn it off.
- I'm trying.

07:20.107 --> 07:21.107
Hello?

07:21.316 --> 07:23.152
Charlie? It's bif.

07:23.277 --> 07:24.629
<i>Is now a good time?</i>

07:24.653 --> 07:27.531
Uh, couldn't be better.

07:28.240 --> 07:30.677
<i>Some chancer took a
fancy to my handbag.</i>

07:30.701 --> 07:32.786
Would you be a love and
drop off my spare keys?

07:33.036 --> 07:35.414
Yeah, I'll be there right away.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.541
Thank you, pru.

07:37.791 --> 07:40.294
I really must get around
to buying one of these.

07:40.586 --> 07:43.672
Why, when you can just
borrow other people's.

07:46.008 --> 07:47.342
Did you get a good look at him?

07:47.593 --> 07:49.511
No.

07:49.845 --> 07:52.445
By the time I made it to the top
of the hill, I was seeing double.

07:52.598 --> 07:53.682
Say when.

07:54.057 --> 07:55.684
Woo-hoo-hoo! When! When! When!

07:56.310 --> 07:59.646
Shame about the bag, though.
I got it in Italy years ago.

07:59.771 --> 08:00.814
Hmm.

08:02.316 --> 08:03.460
What's that for?

08:03.484 --> 08:05.027
Oh, it's to cover your pension.

08:05.402 --> 08:07.255
- Put it away, Charlie.
- Oh, bif.

08:07.279 --> 08:08.739
- Please, please.
- No, come on.

08:09.156 --> 08:12.051
I lost my bus pass and a couple
of sachets of laxatives.

08:12.075 --> 08:13.076
All right.

08:13.410 --> 08:16.205
Does make you wonder why they
go to all that bother, though.

08:16.747 --> 08:19.541
Well, constipation.
It's a terrible thing.

08:44.983 --> 08:46.543
Right, we're here, love.
You all right?

08:48.278 --> 08:49.278
Yes.

08:49.613 --> 08:51.114
That'll be Â£37.50.

08:51.949 --> 08:53.075
Right.

08:56.745 --> 08:58.455
Keep a pound for yourself.

08:59.164 --> 09:00.924
I should really charge
you corkage, you know.

09:05.003 --> 09:07.774
Would you be so kind as to
carry my bags up to the door?

09:07.798 --> 09:10.509
Do me a favour, darling, I'm
a cab driver, not a footman.

09:17.015 --> 09:18.100
Please.

09:19.601 --> 09:20.686
Thank you, excuse me.

09:22.479 --> 09:24.690
Thank you. Thank you, thank you.

09:27.276 --> 09:30.862
Any chance you could fix the front
window lock for me before you go?

09:32.406 --> 09:34.366
- I'd leave it.
- Why?

09:34.616 --> 09:37.016
With a bit of luck, somebody
might climb in and take the lot.

09:53.802 --> 09:55.512
Elizabeth, it's Sandra.

09:58.181 --> 10:01.661
Sandra! What a lovely surp...
What are you doing here?

10:01.685 --> 10:04.414
Mike's been having an affair with
Pamela Harper so I've left him.

10:04.438 --> 10:07.358
I tried calling your landline, but
apparently, you've changed your number.

10:07.382 --> 10:09.335
- Years ago.
- You might have let me know.

10:09.359 --> 10:11.403
I expect it's been
cut off anyway, now.

10:12.237 --> 10:13.357
Or perhaps you've buried it.

10:16.491 --> 10:19.119
I can only imagine what
everyone is saying back home.

10:19.661 --> 10:21.472
Now I know we weren't exactly
in our honeymoon period,

10:21.496 --> 10:23.976
but I just imagined his libido
had naturally declined with age,

10:24.000 --> 10:26.352
but it turns out he's been
bonking her behind my back

10:26.376 --> 10:27.937
- for over five years.
- Oh.

10:27.961 --> 10:29.689
I mean, what has she got
that I haven't got?

10:29.713 --> 10:31.340
She's a mistress, Sandra.

10:31.632 --> 10:34.152
- It's a fantasy.
- It's not a bloo... this is bloody real.

10:34.176 --> 10:36.136
Aren't you going to
offer me a drink?

10:36.470 --> 10:37.470
Oh, sorry.

10:38.180 --> 10:39.848
Um, well,

10:40.265 --> 10:41.350
I've got

10:41.642 --> 10:43.560
- peach Brandy or grappa?
- Yes, please.

10:43.769 --> 10:46.289
Well, that should stop anybody
rummaging in your drawers.

10:46.313 --> 10:47.356
I should be so lucky.

10:48.440 --> 10:49.792
- Hello.
- Charlie,

10:49.816 --> 10:51.526
this is my little
sister, Sandra.

10:51.652 --> 10:53.445
Oh, it's nice to meet you.

10:55.489 --> 10:57.074
- Lady abbott.
- Oh.

10:57.616 --> 10:58.700
Honoured even.

10:59.743 --> 11:00.786
All right, well, uh,

11:01.536 --> 11:03.890
sounds like you've got a
lot of catching up to do.

11:03.914 --> 11:06.458
Uh, I'll see you on
Thursday, dear, all right?

11:09.211 --> 11:10.295
Bye.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.384
Lady abbott?

11:24.101 --> 11:26.228
I know it doesn't feel
like it at the moment,

11:26.478 --> 11:29.022
but this could be the best thing
that ever happened to you.

11:29.773 --> 11:32.859
A chance to finally step
out from Mike's shadow.

11:33.235 --> 11:34.361
What do you mean?

11:35.529 --> 11:36.530
Excuse me.

11:36.655 --> 11:38.841
Do you have, er,
spoons or forks,

11:38.865 --> 11:41.719
anything that resembles
actual cutlery here?

11:41.743 --> 11:43.203
Another one of those.

11:44.246 --> 11:47.100
I always found him overbearing,
smug and self-important.

11:47.124 --> 11:49.334
Classic case of
small-man syndrome.

11:49.459 --> 11:51.461
My husband doesn't
have a small penis.

11:53.755 --> 11:56.883
I wasn't actually referring
to his genitalia, Sandra.

11:57.926 --> 11:59.570
I just wondered why
a man of his size

11:59.594 --> 12:01.531
got into the police force
in the first place.

12:01.555 --> 12:04.182
There was a minimum height
amnesty for a couple of years.

12:04.766 --> 12:07.328
That still doesn't excuse you
from sleeping with the enemy.

12:07.352 --> 12:09.455
The whole point of us
going to greenham common

12:09.479 --> 12:12.441
was to stand side by side
in female solidarity.

12:13.275 --> 12:16.421
You dropped your knickers at the first
suggestive glance through the fence.

12:16.445 --> 12:18.673
Mike was only doing his job.

12:18.697 --> 12:21.050
Guarding a bloody
nuclear weapon.

12:21.074 --> 12:23.261
It was the height of the
cold war, people were scared

12:23.285 --> 12:26.264
and they had every right to believe
that they needed a nuclear deterrent.

12:26.288 --> 12:28.224
- Poppycock.
- Can you not appreciate

12:28.248 --> 12:30.643
that not everyone is as brave
and self-sufficient as you?

12:30.667 --> 12:35.940
Some of us need to feel safe and secure
which is exactly what Mike offered me.

12:35.964 --> 12:38.133
Until he decided to
press the red button.

12:40.510 --> 12:42.155
I knew it was a
mistake coming here.

12:42.179 --> 12:44.460
How could I have expected you
of all people to understand?

12:44.484 --> 12:47.535
You've never stuck at a relationship
in your life because it takes you away

12:47.559 --> 12:51.038
from your devotion to yourself
and your latest crackpot cause.

12:51.062 --> 12:54.041
There's nothing crackpot about
trying to safeguard the planet.

12:54.065 --> 12:56.919
Oh, right, so what would
happen to the human race

12:56.943 --> 13:00.757
if everyone was too busy saving the
planet to make time to procreate?

13:00.781 --> 13:03.885
Oh, so the universe should be grateful
that you and Mike had a knee trembler?

13:03.909 --> 13:06.262
Ladies, could you
please quieten down?

13:06.286 --> 13:08.806
You're upsetting the
other customers.

13:08.830 --> 13:10.308
We're upsetting them?

13:10.332 --> 13:12.935
How about the lifetime of
heartbreak and betrayal

13:12.959 --> 13:15.062
that is inevitably
coming their way?

13:15.086 --> 13:17.899
Not that I would expect you to
understand with your cultural concubines

13:17.923 --> 13:18.924
and polygamy.

13:19.382 --> 13:21.235
I'm going to have to
ask you to leave!

13:21.259 --> 13:22.928
I beg your... how dare...

13:26.264 --> 13:28.493
Officers, there's been a
terrible misunderstanding.

13:28.517 --> 13:30.828
I was simply having a
very nice conversation

13:30.852 --> 13:33.206
- with the young manager there.
- Keep going.

13:33.230 --> 13:35.500
And when the, uh, my hand
inadvertously slipped...

13:35.524 --> 13:38.044
- Will you get your hands off me?
- All right, madam, calm down.

13:38.068 --> 13:40.546
I do hope you know who
you're dealing with.

13:40.570 --> 13:44.533
I'm married to the former chief
constable of surrey police.

13:46.201 --> 13:48.286
Her husband's been
cheating on her.

13:49.037 --> 13:50.413
I'm not surprised.

13:54.835 --> 13:56.437
What did they charge you with?

13:56.461 --> 13:58.922
Racial aggravation or
drunk and disorderly?

13:59.381 --> 14:02.026
Could we discuss this
in a less public forum?

14:02.050 --> 14:04.970
Sure, I'm coming down. Chuck
this in the bins, will you?

14:15.981 --> 14:19.651
I came down to the station, but
they said you were sleeping it off.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.152
This isn't funny, bif.

14:21.653 --> 14:24.013
If you hadn't been bullying me,
I wouldn't have got so upset

14:24.037 --> 14:25.716
and thrown the onion
bhaji at that woman.

14:25.740 --> 14:28.761
It was a man and you assaulted
him with a prawn dumpling.

14:28.785 --> 14:30.304
Why are you being so pernickety?

14:30.328 --> 14:33.790
Listen, why don't you have an
alka-seltzer, have a lie down,

14:33.915 --> 14:35.393
and I'll be back this afternoon.

14:35.417 --> 14:37.085
- Why? Where are you going?
- Dancing.

14:50.432 --> 14:52.910
Very good! Good, good, good!
And turn!

14:52.934 --> 14:55.228
Turn! Flick! Flick!

14:58.064 --> 15:00.233
- Flick! Flick! Flick!
- Flick!

15:01.735 --> 15:04.088
- Sorry, corrinna.
- Oh, no worries. You're with Ted.

15:04.112 --> 15:05.822
I've worked out some
new moves for us.

15:07.032 --> 15:09.117
Might want to put your
crash helmet back on.

15:13.288 --> 15:14.331
Very nice.

15:16.541 --> 15:18.209
Good, good! Sheila, great!

15:39.147 --> 15:40.148
Hello?

15:40.273 --> 15:41.733
<i>Sandra, it's me.</i>

15:42.734 --> 15:43.902
Oh, yes.

15:44.986 --> 15:46.655
Pamela's asked me to
move in with her.

15:47.614 --> 15:49.532
She wants us to make a
fresh start together.

15:50.784 --> 15:51.784
I thought it through,

15:52.452 --> 15:54.913
and I've decided it's in
everyone's best interest.

15:55.622 --> 15:57.040
How very bloody
thoughtful of you.

15:57.415 --> 15:59.459
Sandra, I hope that with time,

15:59.960 --> 16:02.921
you'll understand that I
never set out to hurt you.

16:03.713 --> 16:06.466
Hurt me? How about
bloody destroyed me?

16:27.487 --> 16:29.531
Okay, everyone,
let's take a break.

16:36.162 --> 16:39.541
- Oh, I'll never get it.
- Yeah. Here you go, Ted.

16:40.083 --> 16:41.918
Payment for your
labour the other day.

16:42.377 --> 16:44.754
What? Danger money, you mean.

16:45.213 --> 16:46.631
Oh, put it away.

16:47.215 --> 16:49.592
How did your Internet
date go at the weekend?

16:50.260 --> 16:52.380
Well, let's just say, I got
more than I bargained for.

16:52.404 --> 16:55.199
- Ooh, lucky you.
- No, he showed up with his wife in tow.

16:55.557 --> 16:59.102
Turns out I'd clicked swinging instead
of swimming on my list of likes.

17:14.451 --> 17:15.743
Ooh.

17:24.461 --> 17:27.064
These old locks are a bloody...

17:27.088 --> 17:29.924
You don't fancy changing the
one on my front door, do you?

17:32.260 --> 17:35.305
Oh, how you and her
majesty are sisters,

17:36.514 --> 17:37.658
I'll never know.

17:37.682 --> 17:39.618
Well, she used to be fun.

17:39.642 --> 17:41.311
Oh, yeah? What happened?

17:42.479 --> 17:43.980
She married a tosser,

17:44.147 --> 17:47.233
and then became obsessed with
keeping up with all the tossers.

17:49.319 --> 17:51.863
When was the last time you
saw one another, then?

17:52.572 --> 17:55.366
Erm, it's nearly ten years.

17:56.826 --> 17:59.954
I was protesting against
the newbury bypass.

18:01.998 --> 18:04.101
- Yeah?
- I failed to turn up

18:04.125 --> 18:06.479
- to her 50th birthday...
- Oh, dear.

18:06.503 --> 18:08.939
- And it was a murder mystery party...
- Oh!

18:08.963 --> 18:11.734
And I was the one who ended
up getting killed off.

18:11.758 --> 18:13.259
Yeah.

18:14.427 --> 18:15.970
Ah, I've got it, that's it.

18:17.931 --> 18:22.185
Well, you know, maybe this is an
opportunity for you to get to know

18:22.310 --> 18:23.895
one another again, eh?

18:24.729 --> 18:26.898
Ah, I think we're too stubborn,

18:27.232 --> 18:28.817
and set in our ways.

18:30.568 --> 18:33.029
You? Stubborn? Oh...

18:37.117 --> 18:39.119
- Here you are.
- No, thanks. I've had enough.

18:41.162 --> 18:42.162
Oh.

18:42.330 --> 18:44.457
- It's ringing.
- Yeah, they do that.

18:44.874 --> 18:46.876
- Uh, can you, erm...
- What?

18:48.002 --> 18:49.522
- How does it go...
- What? What is it?

18:49.546 --> 18:51.023
- Uh...
- That up there.

18:51.047 --> 18:52.900
- Okay.
- Well, speak into it.

18:52.924 --> 18:54.193
What? Okay.

18:54.217 --> 18:55.635
He... yes, hello?

18:55.760 --> 18:56.845
Yes?

18:58.012 --> 18:59.012
Oh.

18:59.973 --> 19:03.226
Okay. Um, well, thanks
for letting me know.

19:04.352 --> 19:05.395
I'm on my way.

19:07.021 --> 19:08.523
- What?
- Sandra's in hospital.

19:10.692 --> 19:12.735
I'm not surprised you're
having panic attacks.

19:14.362 --> 19:16.962
- What, with the stress of everything.
- It wasn't a panic attack.

19:16.986 --> 19:19.267
I'm not that sort of a person.
I just had a bit of a turn.

19:19.291 --> 19:21.585
Ready to board the fun bus?

19:22.370 --> 19:25.832
- Er, you go first, Sandra.
- Please come, come, come. This way.

19:27.167 --> 19:29.186
Um, shall I get in first?

19:29.210 --> 19:31.290
- 'Cause there's no seat.
- In you go. Help yourself.

19:31.314 --> 19:32.774
Shut the door. Let's get off.

19:36.843 --> 19:37.844
Right.

19:39.554 --> 19:40.763
Slide her across.

19:45.310 --> 19:47.079
Off we go. Oops.

19:47.103 --> 19:48.855
Are you both high?

