41:56.139 --> 41:58.433
Maybe it's better for
Lilly if I, er...

41:59.643 --> 42:01.102
Don't come any more.

42:06.274 --> 42:07.526
Is that a bad idea?

42:09.402 --> 42:11.571
There's no right or wrong
in these situations.

42:12.656 --> 42:17.285
Look, you sold your house
to care for her, Charlie.

42:18.328 --> 42:20.205
No one could have
done anything more.

42:45.522 --> 42:46.690
Hello, love.

42:58.868 --> 43:01.121
Huh.

43:21.224 --> 43:22.475
Take care, love.

43:45.498 --> 43:46.541
Charlie?

43:48.960 --> 43:49.960
Charlie?

43:50.879 --> 43:53.340
I was just passing and
I thought maybe...

43:53.882 --> 43:56.968
Oh, wish you'd get this
bloody door sorted.

44:01.514 --> 44:02.599
What's up?

44:06.436 --> 44:08.897
Er, it was time to say goodbye.

44:10.774 --> 44:12.317
I'm so sorry, Charlie.

44:14.069 --> 44:15.111
Thanks, uh...

44:15.362 --> 44:16.821
Me too.

44:19.032 --> 44:20.283
You know, I...

44:22.869 --> 44:24.829
I spent my whole life

44:25.997 --> 44:27.874
fixing things, bif, you know?

44:29.876 --> 44:30.919
Uh...

44:31.378 --> 44:32.587
Pretty good at it.

44:37.717 --> 44:38.760
But there's nothing...

44:40.762 --> 44:44.075
Abs... absolutely nothing,

44:44.099 --> 44:45.475
nothing I could...

44:46.101 --> 44:48.520
I can do to fix... fix her.

44:52.649 --> 44:53.983
I'm sorry.

44:57.654 --> 45:00.699
How dare you do this to me?
I hate you so much!

45:50.081 --> 45:51.166
Aah!

45:58.923 --> 46:00.860
Oh, didn't hear you come in.

46:00.884 --> 46:03.303
Just walked in the door.
I got us a curry.

46:05.513 --> 46:07.098
You seem more upbeat today.

46:08.016 --> 46:11.060
Oh, I just got this annoying
tune going round in my head.

46:32.248 --> 46:33.708
Hmm, this one's for you.

46:34.959 --> 46:35.959
Hmm.

46:36.711 --> 46:37.711
Oh.

46:39.255 --> 46:40.548
More bills.

46:44.969 --> 46:46.221
What's the matter?

46:50.099 --> 46:51.434
Divorce petition.

46:52.477 --> 46:54.062
Well, weren't you
expecting that?

46:57.607 --> 46:59.275
What did you think
was gonna happen?

47:01.945 --> 47:03.785
Well, I thought he would
come to his senses and

47:05.698 --> 47:08.034
phone me up and beg
me to come home and

47:08.910 --> 47:10.370
so I could get on with my life.

47:10.745 --> 47:12.580
Oh, surely you
wouldn't have gone?

47:13.373 --> 47:15.500
I know you think I'm
mad, bif, but I've...

47:16.075 --> 47:18.395
I've loved Mike for most of my
life and whatever he's done,

47:18.419 --> 47:20.046
those feelings don't just...

47:22.298 --> 47:23.298
Go away.

47:23.716 --> 47:24.884
Nor this.

47:26.261 --> 47:28.054
You need to get an
expert opinion.

47:30.515 --> 47:31.975
What about him
selling the house?

47:32.642 --> 47:34.519
Well, if the bastard wants
to sell it, let him.

47:34.686 --> 47:37.456
Then Sandra could buy something
smaller with her share.

47:37.480 --> 47:39.983
And live comfortably off
the remaining equity.

47:41.276 --> 47:43.903
The good news is, you get
first dibs of the contents.

47:44.696 --> 47:47.258
All he's requested is the
elizabethan dining table,

47:47.282 --> 47:50.577
six cut glass tumblers,
and his tennis trophies.

47:51.077 --> 47:53.997
35 years of marriage, and
that's all he values?

47:55.456 --> 47:57.768
I'm sorry, Sandra, that was
shockingly clumsy of me.

47:57.792 --> 47:59.794
But I can still keep my title?

48:01.004 --> 48:02.797
I'm afraid it's not
your title, Sandra.

48:03.381 --> 48:06.509
When the marriage is dissolved, it will
be transferred to his chosen consort.

48:10.471 --> 48:13.933
Surely becoming a free woman is
better than being a kept lady.

48:23.985 --> 48:26.946
Good god, this place is obscene.

48:28.072 --> 48:30.158
- Did you have staff?
- You're looking at her.

48:30.325 --> 48:31.326
Oh.

48:31.492 --> 48:34.370
When we bought this house, I
thought we'd be here forever.

48:37.665 --> 48:38.665
Janet.

48:39.584 --> 48:40.811
What are you doing here?

48:40.835 --> 48:43.480
Sandra, what a surprise!

48:43.504 --> 48:46.984
No, I was just collecting some
spare balls from your court.

48:47.008 --> 48:50.404
I thought you wouldn't mind, for
the annual tennis tournament,

48:50.428 --> 48:51.429
this afternoon.

48:51.888 --> 48:53.741
Janet, this is my
sister, Elizabeth.

48:53.765 --> 48:54.933
Bif, hi.

48:55.767 --> 48:57.226
How long are you back for?

48:57.393 --> 48:59.413
Just the day, I'm collecting
some personal things

48:59.437 --> 49:01.373
from the house before
it's shown to buyers.

49:01.397 --> 49:05.568
I know. We saw it had gone on the market.
Such a shame.

49:06.152 --> 49:08.738
After all that work you'd
done with the patio.

49:08.947 --> 49:10.907
But still, you know,
life goes on.

49:12.492 --> 49:16.329
Maybe I'll find a minute to pop over and
say hello to the gang, before we leave.

49:17.038 --> 49:18.539
Oh, that would be a bit awkward.

49:19.666 --> 49:20.917
Mike is coming.

49:22.001 --> 49:23.002
And Pamela.

49:23.544 --> 49:27.173
Sadly, as much as one loves playing with
balls, one's rather pressed for time.

49:31.678 --> 49:36.099
No wonder you stuck it out for so long.
You must have barely seen one another.

49:37.392 --> 49:39.477
And what's with all
this silverware?

49:41.854 --> 49:43.606
It's like a bloody shrine.

49:44.649 --> 49:47.527
I used to spend hours
polishing those.

49:49.153 --> 49:51.781
And I think...

49:53.825 --> 49:56.619
Yes, from that tournament on,
he was sleeping with her.

49:58.663 --> 50:00.957
Well, he doesn't deserve
any prizes for that.

50:07.714 --> 50:09.817
- Come on, your turn!
- No, I can't!

50:09.841 --> 50:11.217
Just do it.

50:12.301 --> 50:14.262
Go on, Sandra. Give it to him.

50:20.435 --> 50:21.894
How does that make you feel?

50:22.770 --> 50:25.770
Well, I was gonna... I was gonna say
better than sex, but it's been so long,

50:25.794 --> 50:27.087
I've forgotten what it's like.

50:28.860 --> 50:30.194
Was Mike a good lover?

50:30.987 --> 50:32.697
I... I think so.

50:33.823 --> 50:36.159
Please tell me there
was life before Mike?

50:39.746 --> 50:42.749
No wonder you put all
that crap on a pedestal.

50:45.835 --> 50:47.545
- Hello.
- Hi.

50:48.046 --> 50:49.314
What are they doing here?

50:49.338 --> 50:51.025
Well, you needed a
man with a Van.

50:51.049 --> 50:52.675
I got you two for
the price of one.

50:59.307 --> 51:01.434
Charlie, I think I
owe you an apology.

51:02.894 --> 51:04.103
I must have come across

51:04.937 --> 51:06.481
quite rude when we first met.

51:06.773 --> 51:08.608
Ah, it's already forgotten.

51:10.276 --> 51:13.005
Anyway, I know how
disorientating it can be

51:13.029 --> 51:14.781
when you find
yourself on your own.

51:16.199 --> 51:17.492
Does it get any easier?

51:19.118 --> 51:20.118
I hope so.

51:20.453 --> 51:23.807
Oi! Are Ted and I the only
ones working around here?

51:23.831 --> 51:24.957
Oh, sorry.

51:25.083 --> 51:28.020
I'll need to report you for an
unscheduled rest break, Charlie.

51:28.044 --> 51:30.147
- You grass!
- Bugger!

51:30.171 --> 51:31.631
- Oh, er, hang on.
- Okay.

51:33.883 --> 51:36.278
Perhaps we should take a
bit of a tea break, eh?

51:36.302 --> 51:37.988
- Yeah.
- Obviously with

51:38.012 --> 51:40.324
- comrade Ted's permission here.
<i>- Da.</i>

51:40.348 --> 51:41.668
Any chance of
something stronger?

51:44.894 --> 51:46.246
Ow! Ooh.

51:46.270 --> 51:47.438
Are you all right?

51:47.730 --> 51:50.900
- I don't fancy being Fred without ginger.
- What?

51:51.442 --> 51:53.587
At the mash-up if you
can't flippin' dance.

51:53.611 --> 51:55.251
The last thing I want
to miss is the fun.

51:55.822 --> 51:58.407
- Worst case, maybe someone else...
- Not happening.

51:59.158 --> 52:00.427
- No.
- Why?

52:00.451 --> 52:02.346
She won't have time
to learn it, anyway.

52:02.370 --> 52:04.970
- She knows it better than I do.
- What difference does that make?

52:06.290 --> 52:08.000
No, it's all right. My treat.

52:08.167 --> 52:09.478
Thank you.

52:09.502 --> 52:10.878
It's my round.

52:11.879 --> 52:13.565
- What do you fancy?
- Yes, ladies.

52:13.589 --> 52:15.526
- Erm, a half of lager, please.
- Half a lager.

52:15.550 --> 52:17.486
- Okay, I'll have a gin and tonic.
- G and t.

52:17.510 --> 52:18.594
Sandra?

52:20.596 --> 52:21.722
What are you doing here?

52:22.598 --> 52:25.351
Just picking up a few souvenirs
from our life together.

52:26.811 --> 52:29.081
Come on, Mikey, let's go.

52:29.105 --> 52:31.875
That's right, run along, pretend
that nothing's happened.

52:31.899 --> 52:33.877
Let's not cause another
scene, Sandra.

52:33.901 --> 52:36.338
Heaven forbid. Perfectly all
right to destroy a marriage,

52:36.362 --> 52:38.173
not okay to talk about it.

52:38.197 --> 52:39.490
Home wrecker.

52:40.241 --> 52:42.052
Home maker, more like.

52:42.076 --> 52:44.054
You may look as
if you're in some

52:44.078 --> 52:49.518
washing powder commercial, but underneath,
you'll always be a grubby little bitch.

52:49.542 --> 52:50.894
Come on, Pamela, let's go.

52:50.918 --> 52:52.170
Come on, leave it.

52:53.713 --> 52:55.607
Whoa! Well, that's her told!

52:55.631 --> 52:57.091
This one's on the house.

52:57.258 --> 52:58.968
Well done!

52:59.927 --> 53:01.095
TouchÃ©.

53:27.788 --> 53:30.225
- Here she is!
- Sorry I'm late. I couldn't find my keys.

53:30.249 --> 53:32.102
- Come on, bif.
- Come on, you lot.

53:32.126 --> 53:34.407
- Are you sure you're up to this?
- Shake a leg! Crack on!

53:34.431 --> 53:37.559
- I better be.
- Yes. Move along, get inside.

53:39.675 --> 53:41.093
Go! Let's go!

53:41.552 --> 53:44.180
- You look nervous, Ted.
- I'm not nervous.

53:44.555 --> 53:47.701
- I'm bloody terrified.
- You'll be fine.

53:47.725 --> 53:48.935
I hope.

53:50.728 --> 53:51.938
Charlie, hang on.

53:53.147 --> 53:55.608
- Room for a small one?
- Yay!

53:57.568 --> 53:59.070
So, you changed your mind, lass.

53:59.278 --> 54:01.948
About a lot of things,
actually, Ted.

